const methodObject = z.object({

});

  property: 3,
  method: function (s: string) {

pull_request.title: Fix/new wallet
pull_request.body:
## Description (optional)
Adds a mix of falling back to IP check for country if nabu user data country isn't available. This will be the case when a user first signs up, is in the wallet, and hasn't started KYC. Next login, nabu user country is set even if user hasn't started KYC.

Also adds logic to check 'signup country' in certain instances. Should cover all cases where the right user will see the warning banners, but there may be cases where non-UK citizens using wallet with UK IP address will see warning banners.

Detail the steps required for the reviewer(s) to verify and test these changes.
